content: Welcome to the 278th edition of Coding Jag http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/um-Email-utm-source-Coding-Jag/fryf1z/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 , brought to you by TestMu AI (Formerly LambdaTest)! Change is constant in software, and so is our focus. What began as a dedication to testing and quality engineering is now expanding to meet the AI era, and TestMu AI embodies that evolution; *it is not a pivot, but a progressive leap*. As development accelerates and intelligence is embedded at every layer, quality must evolve alongside software. TestMu AI, the world's first full-stack Agentic AI Quality Engineering platform, brings autonomous intelligence to every aspect of testing and shapes the future of software quality. In this edition, explore Googles Universal Commerce Protocol for seamless AI-powered shopping, discover the BigQuery MCP Server for building AI data agents, and see how Claude in Microsoft Foundry is advancing healthcare workflows. Learn how GPUs are fueling the [YEAR] AI boom, improve AI outputs with context engineering, and watch Datadogs AI SRE agent accelerate incident resolution and more. Lets jump in NEWS LambdaTest Is Now TestMu AI http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf23/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Were excited to announce an important milestone in our journey. LambdaTest has evolved into TestMu AI, the worlds first full-stack Agentic AI Quality Engineering platform. Under the Hood: Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP) http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf26/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Big news for online shopping and AI builders! Google has introduced the Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP), an open-source standard that lets AI assistants help users discover products, check out, and pay in one smooth flow. Backed by major commerce and payment partners, UCP makes it easier to build secure, AI-powered shopping experiences, a must-try for teams shaping the future of digital commerce. Using the Fully Managed Remote BigQuery MCP Server to Build Data AI Agents http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf29/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Building AI data agents just got easier. Google has launched a fully managed BigQuery MCP server that lets AI agents securely query and analyze enterprise data without heavy setup. By removing custom integrations and infrastructure overhead, this update helps teams move faster, a must-try for anyone creating AI-driven analytics workflows. Bridging the Gap Between AI and Medicine: Claude in Microsoft Foundry Advances Capabilities for Healthcare and Life Sciences Customers http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2d/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 AI for healthcare and life sciences. Steve Sweetman, Azure Product Lead, shares that Claude in Microsoft Foundry now delivers advanced reasoning and agentic workflows for clinical, operational, and research tasks. From prior authorizations to research protocols, Claude helps teams turn complex workflows into actionable insights, a must-try for scaling AI safely in healthcare and life sciences. AI Why Powerful GPUs Are Fueling the Explosive AI Boom in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2h/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 GPUs: The Engine Driving the [YEAR] AI Boom. Rupesh Garg explains how GPUs, with their massive parallel processing, high-bandwidth memory, and cloud accessibility, are powering large language models, generative AI, and real-time AI systems. From faster training to scalable inference, GPU-first architectures are transforming AI development, shaping infrastructure decisions, and defining competitive advantage. A must-try read for anyone building or scaling AI solutions. Want Better AI Outputs? Try Context Engineering http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2l/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Ever wonder how to make GitHub Copilot truly understand your code? Christina Warren shows how context engineering, using custom instructions, reusable prompts, and custom agents, helps Copilot follow your coding standards, automate repeatable tasks, and deliver more accurate, consistent results. A must-try for developers aiming to get smarter AI outputs. How We Built an AI SRE Agent That Investigates Like a Team of Engineers http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2p/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 What if an AI could investigate production incidents like an entire team of SREs? Datadogs Bits AI SRE does just that, autonomously analyzing complex telemetry, forming hypotheses, and tracing root causes with human-like reasoning. By focusing on causal relationships rather than noise, it reduces time to resolution by up to 95%, even in multi-component failures. A must-try for teams aiming to accelerate incident response and reduce downtime. AUTOMATION Automation Framework Configuration With Jenkins and Important of Jenkins in Automation Testing http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2s/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Wondering how teams deliver software faster and more reliably? Yuvraj Rathod shows how configuring Jenkins for automation testing, leveraging parameterized projects, Git integration, build pipelines, and automated email reports, helps teams catch bugs early, streamline CI/CD workflows, and scale testing across environments. A must-try for QA engineers and developers looking to supercharge software delivery. The Real Cost of a Slow CI Build http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2w/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Does your CI build silently sabotage your teams productivity? Dennis Martinez reveals how average builds of 20+ minutes, constant context switching, and a lack of pipeline ownership lead to larger commits, skipped tests, eroded code quality, and declining team morale. A must-read for engineers and managers looking to optimize CI efficiency and keep software delivery flowing smoothly. Automating Push Notification Testing with Appium http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf2z/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Tired of manually testing push notifications across devices and OS versions? Irfan Mujagic shows how Appium, combined with Kotlin and TestNG, can automate sending, verifying, and tapping notifications, ensuring your app responds correctly. A must-read for mobile QA engineers and developers aiming to save time, reduce errors, and build reliable, repeatable tests. How to Build Android Widgets With .NET MAUI http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf33/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Want to build interactive Android widgets directly in .NET MAUI? Toine de Boer explains how to create static and configurable widgets, share data between app and widget, handle interactions with PendingIntents, and optimize performance for a smooth user experience. A must-read for developers aiming to enhance their Android apps with fully interactive, cross-platform widgets. TOOLS Types of Data Migration Explained: A Complete Enterprise Guide for [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf36/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Planning a data migration in [YEAR] ? Harisha Patangay explains why not all migrations are equal. Structured, unstructured, and semi-structured data each have unique challenges, and strategies like big-bang, phased, or hybrid approaches balance speed, risk, and operational stability. Kanerikas AI-powered FLIP platform and migration accelerators automate discovery, mapping, and transformation, cutting manual work, reducing errors, and modernizing systems from SSRS/Crystal/SQL to Power BI or Fabric faster and safer. Postman Alternative: The Best API Testing Tools to Use in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf39/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 Want a smarter alternative to Postman in [YEAR] ? Himanshu Mandhyan explains why modern API testing demands more than manual requests, highlighting the need for automation, CI/CD integration, and developer-first workflows. He breaks down how tools like Keploy generate tests and mocks automatically from real API traffic, improving coverage while reducing maintenance. A must-read for teams looking to scale reliable API testing in fast-moving development environments. OTHERS From the Question of Guilt to Error Culture http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf3d/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 In this podcast, Richie talks with Katja Radom about how error culture shapes software quality and team trust. They discuss why mistakes often trigger blame instead of learning, and how clearly defining what a bug means, how its reported, and how teams respond can reduce conflict and improve outcomes. Katja shares practical insights on leadership as a role model, giving and receiving feedback, and using retrospectives and learning time to turn errors into improvements. A grounded episode that shows how small, consistent actionsnot sloganshelp teams build openness, psychological safety, and better software under real-world pressure. TestMu AI: The Next Chapter! http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-278/fryf3h/ [PHONE] /h/GZrSpCTZ-3MgMpHGb6UU-Gi1kH008RkHz-aDwEhjfy4 In this video, the TestMu AI team unveils the next chapter of LambdaTests evolution, now reimagined as TestMu AI, the worlds first full-stack Agentic AI Quality Engineering platform. The video explains why traditional automation is no longer enough and how TestMu AI moves testing from automation to autonomy, with intelligent agents working alongside teams to keep releases reliable at scale. A crisp introduction to how quality is being redefined for the AI era. content: "Intuit Mailchimp" Were changing contact and send volume limits for the Free Marketing plan on February 17th Thank you for being a part of the Intuit Mailchimp community. We are grateful that youve entrusted us to help support and grow your brand. Were writing to let you know about changes were making to the Free Marketing plan. On February 17th, the plan will have new limits on contacts and send volume. Based on your accounts current contact amount and recent sending volume, youre not immediately impacted by this change. If your contact or sending needs increase, heres how these changes could affect you or any other account on a Free Marketing plan you have. What's changing *Contact limit Up to 250 contacts *Monthly send limit Up to 500 email sends *Daily send limit Up to 250 email sends The features on the Free Marketing plan arent changing. What to expect You currently have fewer than 250 contacts, and you havent recently sent more than 500 emails in a month, so you wont be affected by this change right away. If you exceed 250 contacts in the future, youll need to archive contacts to reach 250 or fewer contacts, or upgrade to a paid plan to continue sending emails. Likewise, if you want to send more than 500 emails per month or more than 250 emails a day, you can switch to a plan that meets your sending needs. Resources To see a list of features for each plan, or calculate pricing based on your sending needs, visit our pricing page . If you have any questions, our pricing plan resource answers many common questions about our plans and billing. A pacincia encurta. O sono fragmenta. A mente perde foco. O corpo parece sempre "um pouco a menos" do que deveria estar. Muita gente interpreta isso como estresse, idade, excesso de trabalho ou falha pessoal. Ou at entende que o calor. Mas o que esto fazendo para mudar isso? Entenda, h outra leitura possvel para essa sensao. No Ayurveda, o vero no apenas uma estao quente. Ele um perodo que consome energia vital, desidrata os tecidos e sobrecarrega a mente quando seguimos vivendo como se nada tivesse mudado. Ou vivendo mantendo a mesma rotina das estaes anteriores. Escrevemos um texto para explicar isso com clareza, com oritentaes de como passar pelo Vero e chegar no outono com mais sade e felicidade. content: O livro ** S Um Jogo, escrito por Edu Moreira,**provocou muita gente. Fez perguntas incmodas,mostrou que muita coisa que parece normal , na verdade, parte de um jogo que a gente aprende a jogar sem perceber. Mas teve algo que ficou claro depois do livro: essas conversas no terminam na ltima pgina. Foi da que nasceu o **retiro presencial S Um Jogo" que vai acontecer do dia 27/02 [MONEY] /03 em So Roque, a 50 min da capital de So Paulo**. A ideia foi simples e direta: tirar as reflexes feitas com a Inteligncia Artificial do papel e lev-las para uma experincia **presencial**, com tempo e conversa real longe do ritmo automtico do dia a dia. Durante alguns dias, um grupo pequeno vai se reunir com Edu Moreira e Marco Schultz para aprofundar essas ideias, trocar experincias e viver aquilo que o livro prope. E justamente por ser presencial, com estrutura real e limite de pessoas, a equipe do ICL preparou **condies especiais de participao**, com **ofertas e descontos exclusivos** que no vo existir depois. Nada disso est sendo divulgado publicamente. Todas as informaes sobre o retiro, como formato, datas, valores, ofertas e acesso s vagas, esto sendo compartilhadas **exclusivamente em um grupo fechado de WhatsApp**. no grupo que a oportunidade ser apresentada do jeito certo. **>>>>>>> CLIQUE AQUI PARA ENTRAR NO GRUPO DE WHATSAPP E RECEBER TODAS AS INFORMAES** https://icl.com.br/lp/ip01-schultz/?act=1150090&acl=410 Se o livro j te fez pensar, essa pode ser a chance de viver a experincia. content: Welcome to the 277th edition of Coding Jag http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/um-Email-utm-source-Coding-Jag/fry663/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU , brought to you by LambdaTest! Even as AI accelerates automation, strong QA teams remain essential. They ensure AI models are safe, scalable, and free from hidden defects, bias, and compliance risks. By combining AI-driven testing with skilled QA practices, organizations maintain trust, reliability, and control. In this edition, explore the latest updates in OpenObserve v0.40.0 for observability teams, see how AI can protect growing codebases, learn to use Promptfoo hooks for dynamic LLM testing, and uncover why AI hasnt yet simplified GTM workflows. Plus, enjoy an insightful podcast, a hands-on video on boosting exploratory testing, and the scoop on upcoming events. Lets jump in NEWS Major Product Update! OpenObserve v0.40.0 http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry666/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Big news for observability teams! Simran Kumari and Jake Swiss share that OpenObserve v0.40.0 has landed as a milestone release. It introduces incident correlation, smarter Auto SQL dashboards, MCP support, Alerts Module 2.0, and a revamped metrics experience. With performance and UI/UX improvements, this update helps teams analyze and act on data faster, making it essential for anyone looking to improve observability workflows. Microsofts Strategic AI Datacenter Planning Enables Seamless, Large-Scale NVIDIA Rubin Deployments http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry669/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Experimenting at scale just got easier! Rani Borkar, President of Azure Hardware Systems and Infrastructure at Microsoft, announced that Azures AI datacenters are fully prepared for the large-scale deployment of NVIDIAs next-generation Rubin platform. Unveiled at CES [YEAR] , this milestone reflects years of strategic co-design with NVIDIA, enabling Rubin systems to integrate seamlessly into Azure. With advanced power, cooling, memory, and ultra-fast networking already in place, Azure can rapidly deploy Rubin NVL72 racks delivering up to 3.6 exaFLOPS per rack, helping teams move faster from experimentation to real-world AI impact. XAML Studio is now Open Sourced http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66d/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU A new chapter for WinUI tooling begins! Michael Hawker announced that XAML Studio has officially gone open source. After years as a proprietary tool, XAML Studio has joined the .NET Foundation, with its v2 codebase now available to the community. This opens the door for developers to contribute new controls, layout tools, experimental editor features, and broader improvements, helping shape the future of WinUI developer tooling. PerceptivePanda Joins Zapier http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66h/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU A notable move in the AI automation space! Navid Zolfaghari shared that Andre Vanier, co-founder of the AI-native platform PerceptivePanda, has joined Zapier to lead Orchestration Strategy. Known for automating customer research interviews with AI, PerceptivePanda delivered valuable insights into real-world AI reliability. Andre now brings this expertise to Zapier, helping customers accelerate automation and optimize AI-driven workflows. AI AI-Driven Test Automation for AWS Glue ETL Pipelines: A Practical Framework for Catching Schema Drift and Hidden Data Quality Issues http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66l/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU What if your ETL tests could catch what SQL misses? Srikanth Kavuri shares a practical, AI-driven framework for testing AWS Glue ETL pipelines that uncovers subtle issues like schema drift, misaligned fixed-length records, and hidden data anomalies. By combining lightweight AI with traditional validation techniques, this approach helps teams detect problems earlier, reduce debugging time, and maintain confidence in complex data workflows. Protecting a Growing TypeScript Codebase With AI Test Generation: How ExpressoTS Used Early http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66p/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Why do you need to protect a growing codebase? Sharon Barr shares how ExpressoTS used Early, an AI [CODE] agent, to automatically write unit tests across their expanding TypeScript repository. By moving from function-level prompts to codebase-level understanding, Early uncovered hidden bugs, boosted test coverage to nearly 90% in hours, and turned testing into a true protection layer, helping maintainers confidently evolve the framework without slowing development. AI Was Supposed to Make GTM Easier. What Went Wrong? http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66s/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Wondering why AI hasnt simplified GTM work? Kyle James shares Jared Robins insight: while AI promised efficiency, many tools added complexity through new workflows, integrations, and roles. As AI became mandatory in [YEAR] , teams struggled to realize real value. In [YEAR] , human-native AI, tools that simplify complexity and fit natural workflows, can help teams focus on judgment, creativity, and strategy. Strong foundations and problem-solving remain the true differentiators in an AI-driven world. AUTOMATION GUI Testing Tools: Best Platforms, Features, and How to Choose http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66w/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Why GUI testing still matters: Michelle Pruitt explains that automated GUI testing ensures consistent, user-friendly interfaces, catches issues early, and reduces human error. Tools like Ranorex, Selenium, Katalon, and Appium provide different strengths, automation styles, and CI/CD support. Choosing the right tool depends on team size, expertise, and workflow needs, helping development teams accelerate releases while maintaining high software quality. Why QA Teams Are Critical for Safe and Scalable AI Integration http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry66z/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Ever Wonder Why QA Teams Are Critical for AI? Rupesh Garg explains that as AI powers core business systems, QA ensures models are safe, reliable, and scalable. AI introduces unique risks, bias, concept drift, hidden defects, and regulatory challenges that require skilled oversight. Modern QA combines test automation, AI-driven validation, regression testing, and continuous monitoring to catch anomalies, maintain compliance, and safeguard performance, enabling organizations to deploy AI confidently and responsibly. Extension Hooks in Promptfoo: Building a Custom LLM Testing Pipeline That Adapts at Runtime http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry673/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Do You Know Why Promptfoo Extension Hooks Matter? Irfan Mujagic explains that Promptfoos extension hooks enable LLM test pipelines to become dynamic and adaptive. Teams can inject tests, modify data at runtime, track metrics, and integrate with CI/CD. Hooks like beforeAll and beforeEach customize test setup, while afterEach and afterAll manage reporting and quality gates, creating flexible, automated workflows for reliable LLM testing. OAuth 2.0 for APIs: Flows, Tokens, and Pitfalls http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry676/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Do You Still Think OAuth 2.0 Matters for APIs? Savan Kharod highlights that OAuth 2.0 lets client apps access APIs securely without exposing user credentials. Key flows like Authorization Code + PKCE, Client Credentials, and Device Authorization fit different clients, while tokens, scopes, and observability ensure least-privilege, secure, and auditable access. TOOLS Data Modernization Services: Top Tools, Benefits, Best Practices in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry679/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Still running AI on legacy data systems? Sagar Uppili explains why data modernization is critical in the AI era. Outdated platforms drain IT budgets, slow decisions, and limit AI potential. Automated migration tools like Kanerikas FLIP help move data to modern stacks such as Power BI, Databricks, or Microsoft Fabric, preserving accuracy while enabling real-time analytics, scalability, and compliance. op 9 Automation Testing Trends for [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry67d/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Why are testers excited about AI, but still cautious? Joe Colantonio shares the top automation testing trends for [YEAR] , revealing a clear paradox: while most teams prioritize AI-driven testing, they dont fully trust it without human review. The findings show that integration challenges, skills gaps, unclear requirements, and compliance concerns outweigh the impact of shiny new tools. The key takeaway for [YEAR] is clear: AI can accelerate testing, but human judgment remains essential. OTHERS Testing Shapes Reality http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry67h/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU In this podcast, Keith Klain reflects on how testing shapes reality in the era of GenAI. He cautions that AI-generated tests can create false confidence by prioritizing volume over intent, risk, and real human experience. Keith explains how tests act as a lens on system quality, and what teams choose to test directly influences business decisions and assumptions. A must-listen episode that urges organizations to keep testers in control, focus on real-world risk, and bring clarity so AI strengthens testing without distorting reality. Boost Your Exploratory Testing - One Tool to Rule Them All http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry67l/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU In this video, Daniel Knott demonstrates Bug Magnet, a free, open-source tool that boosts exploratory testing by inserting edge cases and boundary values directly into web inputs via the browsers context menu. He shows how Bug Magnet works in Chrome and Firefox, how its customizable for different testing needs, and why it helps testers quickly uncover validation issues, edge-case bugs, and potential vulnerabilities without slowing down their workflow. EVENTS PNSQC Quality Jam [YEAR] ! http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-277/fry67p/ [PHONE] /h/DvXteGkuHDSyk6HYqIq6d4ZdgnEKRIUnYWZ99edWEeU Join the software quality community on January 22, [YEAR] , for the PNSQC Quality Jam (Portland, OR + Online), a hybrid lightning-talk event that brings practitioners together to kick off the PNSQC Call for Papers. The event features fast-paced 8-minute talks from industry leaders on software testing, quality engineering, AI, security, and leadership, along with networking and refreshments to spark ideas and conversations for the year ahead. content: Um novo ano chegou, o Natal passou, os presentes j foram trocados e o que fica agora o sentimento de novidade E com esse sentimento, vem junto aquele momento silencioso do ano em que a gente se pergunta: **Que tipo de pessoa eu quero ser daqui pra frente?** [YEAR] no ser um ano simples. E o Brasil no precisa de mais opinies, mas sim de **formao, pensamento crtico e acesso ao conhecimento**. a partir dessa responsabilidade que existe o **plano solidrio do Instituto Conhecimento Liberta**. Ao assinar o **plano solidrio do ICL**, sua escolha vai alm do seu prprio aprendizado. Voc: * garante seu acesso completo plataforma ICL * **doa uma bolsa de estudos** para um jovem em situao de vulnerabilidade * recebe o **Certificado Digital de Membro(a) Doador(a) do ICL**, reconhecendo oficialmente seu compromisso com a educao e a formao crtica no Brasil **>>>>> CLIQUE AQUI E GARANTA AGORA SUA ASSINATURA DO ICL** https://icl.com.br/ Ao assinar o ICL, voc vai concretizar o seu posicionamento e garantir a virada de chave na sua vida e na vida de um jovem. Como Membro solidrio, voc tem acesso a uma das plataformas de conhecimento mais completas do pas com: * **+ de 330 cursos e documentrios**, com curadoria crtica e contedos aprofundados * **Colees de livros digitais** com curadoria da Editora Instituto Conhecimento Liberta, que tratam de aspectos fundamentais da Poltica, Cultura, Economia e Sociedade. * **ICL+, o streaming do ICL,**com acesso irrestrito s nossas produes originais, alm de + de 200 de documentrios internacionais. * **Cursos de 7 lnguas estrangeiras**, ampliando repertrio cultural e possibilidades de futuro * **Clube de benefcios do ICL**, com vantagens exclusivas para membros **>>>>> CLIQUE AQUI E GARANTA AGORA SUA ASSINATURA DO ICL** https://icl.com.br/ Tudo isso enquanto sua assinatura garante que **outro jovem tambm tenha acesso a esse mesmo universo de conhecimento**. Voc vai comear [YEAR] sabendo que: * est investindo na sua prpria formao * sua casa vai se tornar um espao de aprendizado e debate * **e algum que talvez nunca tivesse essa chance comece a mudar sua trajetria atravs do conhecimento** **Educao crtica cria autonomia, autonomia cria cidadania e cidadania constri futuro.** Se voc acredita que o conhecimento precisa circular e que um pas mais justo se constri com mais acesso, no com menos O plano solidrio o seu prximo passo. **>>>>> CLIQUE AQUI E GARANTA AGORA SUA ASSINATURA DO ICL** https://icl.com.br/ Abraos, Equipe ICL Enviado para: [NAME] @gmail.com Cancelar inscrio http://email.institutoliberta.com.br/proc.php?c=28971&m=28992&s=e9d11f7b8c37aeabeccfaa0d827defc3&d=2733809&v=2&nl=92&act=unsub Instituto Conhecimento Liberta, So Paulo, - , Brazil

content: Welcome to the 276th edition of Coding Jag http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/um-Email-utm-source-Coding-Jag/frxzbs/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw , brought to you by LambdaTest! AI is moving beyond a tool; it's becoming a teammate, shaping the way teams collaborate, automate, and make decisions. From autonomous testing to AI-driven workflows, [YEAR] promises a transformative year where AI not only assists but actively drives outcomes. In this edition, discover the latest in AI-driven automation with GPT-5.2 in Microsoft Foundry, explore open-source testing frameworks like Anthropic Bloom, and learn how QA strategies are evolving to scale AI-generated code responsibly and more. Plus, get insights on smarter QA practices, codeless automation tools, VMware alternatives, and upcoming events like SoCraTes Conference Switzerland. But before we jump in Happy Holidays and a fantastic New Year from all of us at LambdaTest! Heres to a [YEAR] full of smarter testing, faster releases, and AI as your new teammate. NEWS LambdaTest [YEAR] Highlights & Whats Next: http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzbw/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw LambdaTest is powering ahead in quality engineering, serving over 15,000 customers and 2.3M + users worldwide. This year, it continues to redefine enterprise testing with AI-driven automation and orchestration, building on recognition such as the [YEAR] Intellyx Digital Innovator Award and its status as a Challenger in the inaugural Gartner Magic Quadrant for AIAugmented Software Testing Tools. With innovations like HyperExecute, KaneAI, and Agent-to-Agent testing driving automation to new heights, LambdaTest is redefining autonomous testing in [YEAR] . The platform empowers teams to accelerate feedback loops, reduce bottlenecks, and ship highquality software faster and smarter. Introducing GPT-5.2 in Microsoft Foundry: The New Standard for Enterprise AI http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzbz/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Imagine AI that doesnt just chat, but truly reasons for enterprise needs. Naomi Moneypenny shares that GPT-5.2 is now generally available in Microsoft Foundry, bringing stronger reasoning, better context awareness, and agentic workflows. Why try it? It helps teams solve complex problems faster with more reliable, auditable results. Testing AI Models with Anthropic Bloom Open Source Tool http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzc3/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Wondering how open-source tools can expose hidden AI behaviors? This article by Software Testing Magazine shares how Anthropics Bloom provides a flexible, seed-driven framework to generate and scale behavioral evaluations across frontier models. Give it a try, as it helps researchers distinguish aligned models from misaligned ones with repeatable, evidence-backed testing. Security at Qodo in [YEAR] : Our Commitment, Recent Learnings, and Whats Next http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzc6/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Confident security doesnt happen by accident. The Qodo team shares how security is a top priority heading into [YEAR] , detailing recent learnings, a responsibly disclosed RCE vulnerability thats now fully remediated, and stronger safeguards ahead. Its a must-read, as it shows how Qodo is raising its security bar with dedicated AppSec hires, external experts, and improved tooling, without impact to customers. AI AI-Generated Code at Enterprise Scale http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzc9/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Can AI-generated code really scale in enterprise production? Sharon Barr explores how rapid vibe coding boosts velocity, but often outpaces trust, testing, and long-term maintainability. As AI code moves from experiments to mission-critical systems, gaps in validation and test quality become the real blockers. It explains why speed alone isnt enough, and what enterprises must fix to make AI-generated code truly durable. 10 AI Predictions for [YEAR] as AI Moves From Tool to Teammate http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzcd/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Curious what happens when AI shifts from tool to true teammate? Matthew Stein shares 10 bold predictions for [YEAR] , covering everything from AI onboarding and hiring to trust, video, ROI, and monetization. Why read on? It challenges where AI hype breaks down, and where real competitive advantage may finally emerge. AUTOMATION Beyond Bug Hunts: Building Real Software Quality Through Smarter Testing http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzch/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw What if software quality wasnt about catching bugs, but about earning user trust? This piece explains how smarter, risk-driven testing shifts QA from a last-minute checkpoint to a system that protects real user experiences, especially in trust-sensitive products like e-learning. Give it a read as it shows how focusing on learning flow, data integrity, and meaningful automation builds software people actually rely on. What Is Beta Testing? Process, Types, Benefits, and Best Practices http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzcl/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Ever wondered how teams catch real-world issues before launch? Alok Kumar explains how beta testing bridges internal QA and real users by validating software in real environments, uncovering usability gaps, device issues, and risks automated tests often miss. Reading this will show you how you can structure beta programs, de-risk launches, improve UX, and build lasting user trust. Modern Data Warehouse Testing Strategy Guide for [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzcp/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Curious how teams can trust analytics as data complexity explodes? The QASource Engineering Team outlines a future-ready Data Warehouse Testing Strategy for [YEAR] , covering automation, AI-driven observability, and end-to-end validation to keep data accurate, secure, and reliable. It shows how smarter testing protects business decisions, reduces costly data errors, and builds confidence in enterprise analytics at scale. The Role of QA in Delivering Exceptional User Experiences http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzcs/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Want to deliver seamless user experiences? David Richard explains that QA is more than bug-finding; its about predicting and preventing user issues before they happen. By validating functionality, performance, usability, and accessibility, QA ensures reliable, fast, and inclusive products. Shift-left practices, automation, and real-world scenario testing keep releases stable, build user trust, and turn QA into a strategic advantage that boosts engagement, conversions, and brand credibility. TOOLS Best 10 VMware Alternatives: The DevOps guide to escaping the "Broadcom Tax" http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzcw/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Worried your app might slow down or crash? Mit Thakkar explains key performance testing services for [YEAR] , from load, stress, spike, and endurance testing to API, mobile, and cloud testing. Advanced tools like AI-driven testing, chaos engineering, and real user monitoring help apps stay fast, stable, and reliable under real-world conditions. Codeless Automation Testing Tools in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxzcz/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw Want faster, easier test automation without coding? Dominik Szahidewicz explains that codeless testing is the answer. By using visual, drag-and-drop interfaces, AI-assisted workflows, and CI/CD integration, teams can create, run, and maintain tests without coding. Key factors, simplified test creation, reduced maintenance, improved coverage, and enhanced collaboration, make tools like BugBug, LambdaTest KaneAI, and others accelerate QA and deliver higher-quality software. OTHERS Ask Me Anything About AI, Automation and Shift Left http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzd3/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw In this podcast, Richard Seidl reviews [YEAR] in software testing, reflecting on 176 episodes, 228 guests, and 300,000 downloads. He discusses AIs evolving role, how it supports but doesnt replace testers, manual testing versus coding skills, meaningful automation, and handling flaky tests. Richard Seidl shares lessons from mistakes, tool choices like Selenium vs. Playwright, and insights from listener questions. He also looks ahead to [YEAR] , focusing on test strategy, soft skills, AI in legacy systems, and growing the international podcast audience. Bringing Androidify to Wear OS http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-276/frxzd6/ [PHONE] /h/QLVrTND8Wbu_RdUzFr1zX7uIYdp7_J6Fvh6iVBwHaJw In this video, Android Developers presents Bringing Androidify to Wear OS, showing how to create personalized Wear OS watch faces from your Android app. The tutorial covers designing templates with Watch Face Designer, transmitting dynamic content via the Watch Face Push API and Data Layer APIs, and steps for packaging, validating, and activating custom watch faces, helping developers enhance engagement on smartwatches. AWS re:Invent, coding with cats, and mayo disasters *************
The Overflow.
************* 24 December Don't let all those year in-review posts
on your social media feeds fool youwe've got plenty of new
stories for you this week. We just got back from AWS re:Invent,
and we've got the skinny on all the new tech announced. Two
podcasts, two different takes. First, our very own CEO Prashanth
Chandrasekar and Director of Data Science Michael Foree joined us
to discuss everything they heard and saw at the event. Corey
Quinn, Chief Cloud Economist at Duckbill and snark king, also sat
down with us to debrief on all things re:Invent, from the new
technology to the restaurants. If you're more of a reader than a
listener, we have a full recap for you on the blog of everything
you'd want to know from re:Invent [YEAR] . Fine, we won't be a Scrooge McDuck...we'll get into the wrapped
spirit too. Let's take a walk down memory lanemaybe with Your [YEAR] Stacked, our fun year-in-review for our Stack Internal
customers. Not your style? No worries. From the web, we've got a
state of AI coding report for you, so you can look back and think
about all the hours you saved (or more likely wasted) with coding
bots. If you want to take it even further back, read about how
they're recovering the lost files of Sega Channel. Maybe you'd
even be interested in the history of your favorite default font,
Times New Roman. If that's too much nostalgia for you, let's wrap this up by
bringing you back to [YEAR] . No Overflow could be complete without
a few questions and a few answers, and this week we've even got
the top ten Q&As of the year from our sites. Plus, we've plenty
moreeverything from melting big pieces of ice to ritualized
workplace confessions and mayo disasters. It's all down below for
you, wrapped and ready to go. -------------
From the blog

Ryan is joined by Stack Overflows CEO Prashanth Chandrasekar and
Director of Data Science Michael Foree on the floor at re:Invent
to discuss all theyve seen and heard at the event, from the

subject: Issue 309: Your year Stacked

content: Welcome to the 275th edition of Coding Jag http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/um-Email-utm-source-Coding-Jag/frxsdw/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 , brought to you by LambdaTest! AI agents are changing how developers tackle real-world tasks, from automating browser actions to managing complex workflows. Gemini 3 makes deploying multi-agent workflows simple, with stateful reasoning, memory management, and autonomous task execution. In this edition, discover how Gemini 3 can streamline repetitive tasks, learn why GitHub Actions was completely re-architected, see how AI browsers are outpacing traditional ones, explore AI code review platforms like Qodo to maintain code quality, and get strategies for smarter test data management and more. Plus, listen to the latest podcasts and register for upcoming virtual events like Agile Tech Talks with Bryan Beecham. Lets jump in! NEWS Next Edit Suggestions: Now Generally Available http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsdz/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 What if your IDE could suggest better code edits as you work? Anton Semenkin reveals that JetBrains Next Edit Suggestions are now generally available for AI Pro, Ultimate, and Enterprise users. NES offers smart, in-editor diffs that refine your code with low latency and no AI quota usage. Built on a custom cloud model and native IDE intelligence, it complements code completion, helping you achieve cleaner code, fewer manual refactors, and a faster coding flow. Lets Talk About GitHub Actions http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsf3/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 What happens when GitHub completely rebuilds the engine behind your CI/CD? Ben De St Paer-Gotch explains how GitHub re-architected the core of GitHub Actions to handle massive scale, now powering 71 million jobs per day, while delivering long-awaited improvements like YAML anchors, deeper reusable workflows, larger caches, and more flexible workflow inputs. A great read if you want faster, more reliable pipelines and a preview of what GitHub Actions is unlocking next. Introducing AI Title Generation http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsf6/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Tired of vague or duplicated bug titles? Emile-Victor Portenart (Marker.io's CPO) introduces AI Title Generation (beta), which automatically creates clear, actionable titles from a reporters description. By hiding the title field, reporters can focus on describing the issue, while generated titles are sent directly to tools like Jira and Linear, perfect for faster triage, cleaner reports, and smoother collaboration. AI AI Browsers vs Traditional Browsers http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsf9/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 The future of browsing is here. Jesse Anglen highlights AI Agentic Browsers, which go beyond traditional browsers by acting as proactive collaborators, automating tasks, synthesizing research, and generating content. A must-read for anyone looking to boost productivity, navigate the agentic web safely, and adapt to AI-driven Answer Engine Optimization (AEO). The Missing Quality Layer: Qodos AI Code Review Platform http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfd/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Code faster without sacrificing quality. Elana Krasner introduces Qodo, an AI Code Review Platform that fills the missing quality layer in modern development. By bringing context-aware, multi-agent reviews across the IDE, pull requests, and CI/CD pipelines, Qodo identifies bugs, breaking changes, test gaps, and compliance issues before they reach production. A must-read for teams looking to accelerate development while keeping code reliable, consistent, and aligned with organizational standards. AUTOMATION The Definitive Guide to Building a Cross-Browser Testing Matrix for [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfh/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Worried your website works in Chrome but breaks in Safari or Firefox? A cross-browser testing matrix is your blueprint for universal web compatibility in [YEAR] . By analyzing user data, prioritizing critical browser-OS combinations, and combining manual and automated testing in CI/CD pipelines, teams can ensure consistent performance across devices. Regular updates and cloud-based tools like LambdaTest make testing efficient, focused, and future-proof. A must-read for QA teams aiming for flawless user experiences Stop Apologizing for Flaky Tests http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfl/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Flaky tests arent a testers fault; they highlight deeper issues in system design. This article by TestinGil emphasizes focusing on testability: make features easy to run and automate without complex setups. Prioritize observability: ensure failures are clear, actionable, and easy to trace. Rather than constantly patching scripts, involve testers early in design discussions and advocate for architectures that make testing reliable, fast, and effective. Real-World Agent Examples With Gemini 3 http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfp/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Ever wondered how AI agents can perform real-world tasks reliably? Philipp Schmid, Mark McDonald, and Vishal Dharmadhikari show how Gemini 3 powers multi-agent workflows. Using frameworks like ADK, Agno, and Letta, developers can automate browser actions, social media interactions, and enterprise operations. These agents feature stateful reasoning, memory management, and autonomous task execution, ready to clone, run, and customize. Test Data Management for Modern Software Testing http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfs/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Struggling with unreliable tests or inconsistent results? Alok Kumar explains that Test Data Management (TDM) is the solution. By automating data creation, masking sensitive info, centralizing datasets, and integrating with CI/CD, teams ensure consistent, reproducible tests. Tools like Keploy make it easy to generate secure, production-like data, accelerating testing and delivering higher-quality software. TOOLS List of Performance Testing Services Every Business Needs in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfw/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Worried your app might slow down or crash? Mit Thakkar explains key performance testing services for [YEAR] , from load, stress, spike, and endurance testing to API, mobile, and cloud testing. Advanced tools like AI-driven testing, chaos engineering, and real user monitoring help apps stay fast, stable, and reliable under real-world conditions. 5 Podcast Episodes to Help You Build With Confidence in [YEAR] http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsfz/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Looking to build with confidence in [YEAR] ? Cassidy Williams highlights five GitHub Podcast episodes that help developers navigate AI, open source sustainability, smarter workflows, privacy-first tools, and real-world trends. These conversations offer practical insights to create software intentionally, efficiently, and responsibly, while staying connected to the community and emerging technologies. Top 10 DevOps Automation Tools to Streamline Mid-market Infrastructure http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsg3/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Looking to scale your DevOps without expanding your team? Mlanie Dall highlights top DevOps automation tools for mid-market teams, from Terraform, Ansible, and GitHub Actions to Argo CD, Pulumi, and Selenium. All-in-one platforms like Qovery simplify deployment, CI/CD, scaling, and environment management, helping teams move faster, reduce complexity, and maintain robust, reliable infrastructure. OTHERS oftware Testing Christmas Chat [YEAR] utm_medium=Email&utm_campaign=Coding_jag_275 In this podcast, Richie talks with Christian Mercier, Matthias Gross and Wolfgang Sperling about software testing in [YEAR] and whats next. They cover how AI only helps with clear strategies, the growing importance of security, performance, and usability, and why testers need both technical skills and resilience. The episode also highlights community learning, validation in production, and practical tips for navigating AI, cloud, and agile challenges. Now in Android: 123 Android XR, Jetpack Navigation 3, and More! http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsg6/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 In this video, Android Developers presents Now in Android: 123, covering the latest updates in Android development. Dan walks through Android XR, the Android Studio Otter 2 feature drop with Gemini 3, Android 16 QPR2, Jetpack Navigation 3, and performance improvements. A concise guide for developers looking to stay current with Android tools, libraries, and OS enhancements. EVENTS Applying Agile Technical Knowledge to LLM-Assisted Development http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-275/frxsg9/ [PHONE] /h/SxSAoX3gBbK62D6qXQyx5JPq2Vg-fxp0DL2HZvJtu00 Agile Tech Talks: Applying Agile Technical Knowledge to LLM-Assisted Development (Jan 14, [YEAR] , 11:00 AM ET | Virtual) features Bryan Beecham demonstrating how to integrate LLMs into development workflows effectively. Learn strategies to maintain code quality, clarity, and productivity when working with AI-generated code. A must-attend for developers and Agile practitioners looking to combine Agile practices with LLM-assisted development. [YEAR] LambdaTest. content: **No comece o ano com o p direito, mas com os dois ps** Essa frase em outros tempos seria lida como um simples desejo de ano novo, mas ela virou munio para recriar um cenrio extremista antissistema contra tudo e contra todos. A histria de "p direito" s mais uma cortina de fumaa. Seu objetivo : **manipular pessoas na midiosfera extremista, atravs de cortes rpidos e descontextualizados que usam do ridculo para entreter e radicalizar**. No se trata de convencer ningum; trata-se de ocupar o espao. **Repensar o Brasil, significa participar dessa disputa de ideias, entendendo que esse tipo de discurso no acontece por acaso.** E se voc quiser entrar com os dois ps nesse debate, temos uma tima notcia! **As inscries da Ps ICL/FESPSP [YEAR] continuam abertas, e com valores promocionais para voc redescobrir o nosso pas**. **Matricule-se na Ps ICL com valores exclusivos e receba em casa uma seleo exclusiva de livros dos nossos professores** https://iclpos.com.br/w05v/ **Estude cincias sociais, filosofia, histria e poltica com um time de professores que no existe em nenhuma universidade tradicional:** **Marilena Chau, Jess Souza, Ladislau Dowbor, Muniz Sodr, Renato Janine [LASTNAME] , Lindener Pareto, Joo Cezar de Castro Rocha, Daniel Munduruku, Joyce Berth e Luiz Felipe de Alencastro** Afinal, esse dio contra as Havaianas no coincidncia. De novo. E devemos estar preparados para o debate de [YEAR] porque como Paulo Freire dizia: **"A leitura do mundo precede a leitura da palavra."** **Escolha um lado e junte-se a mais de 5 mil alunos(as) que mudaram sua viso sobre o Brasil.** https://iclpos.com.br/w05v/ Sua chance de participar dessa luta agora! Com esperana e luta, Equipe Ps ICL Enviado para: [NAME] @gmail.com Cancelar inscrio http://email.institutoliberta.com.br/proc.php?c=28877&m=28909&s=e9d11f7b8c37aeabeccfaa0d827defc3&d=2716089&v=2&nl=92&act=unsub Instituto Conhecimento Liberta, So Paulo, - , Brazil

content: Welcome to the 274th edition of Coding Jag http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/um-Email-utm-source-Coding-Jag/frxjxr/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM , brought to you by LambdaTest! Even a small UI glitch can frustrate users and reduce trust, whether it is on the web or mobile. Cross-browser and cross-device testing is no longer optional; it is essential to catch layout issues, broken functionality, and hidden bugs before your customers experience them. In this edition, discover Googles agent-driven A2UI for building interfaces with AI, streamline QA workflows with Rainforests AI Test Planner, see how Ranorexs Azure DevOps integration can simplify automated test management, and learn how LambdaTest helped a Hospital Management System reduce production incidents by 92%. Also, dont miss out on the amazing AI-driven codebase discovery podcast, watch the latest video on Playwright MCP with SSE/HTTP, and attend the upcoming tech conferences like DevFest Mumbai [YEAR] . NEWS Introducing A2UI: An Open Project for Agent-Driven Interfaces http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-274/frxjxv/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM Imagine AI that builds your interface while you chat. Googles A2UI Team introduces an open, agent-driven framework that generates secure, native-feeling interfaces across platforms. Agents can create forms, charts, maps, and other interactive elements, sent as data, not code, giving clients full control over styling and security. Already powering Opal, Gemini Enterprise, and Flutters GenUI SDK, A2UI is open for developers to explore, extend, and contribute. Enhanced Azure DevOps Test Plans Support Available in Ranorex Studio http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-274/frxjxy/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM Wonder how to manage automated tests directly in Azure DevOps? Ranorex Studio now offers enhanced Test Plans support, letting teams link tests to Azure Test Cases, trigger runs from the Test Plans interface, and automatically publish results back to DevOps. This seamless integration reduces manual steps, improves traceability, and boosts collaboration, helping QA and development teams streamline testing and stay fully aligned with DevOps workflows. Now Available: AI Test Planner - Rainforest Crawls Your App to Deliver a Ready-to-Use Test Plan http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-274/frxjy2/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM Want a smarter way to map your app for QA testing? James Palmer introduces Rainforest QAs AI Test Planner, which automatically explores your app and generates structured test plans. It highlights key features and user journeys, saving time, boosting confidence, and making coverage planning effortless. A must-try for any QA team aiming to plan smarter and faster. AI Learning AI Should Start Before You Feel Ready http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-274/frxjy5/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM Curious about becoming an AI builder? Progress comes from taking the first step, iterating, and staying curious, whether youre experimenting for work, play, or learning new skills. A must-read for anyone ready to explore AI without waiting to feel ready. AUTOMATION How a Hospital Management System Platform Eliminated 92% of Production Incidents http://go.pardot.com/e/1061002/il-utm-campaign-Coding-jag-274/frxjy8/ [PHONE] /h/RYc1_-wLfuMdkg7BNqH-oPQavJ8_vtA61EyAipt0JUM See how a Hospital Management System revolutionized QA with LambdaTests Real Device Cloud and HyperExecute. By expanding device coverage to 10,000+ real devices, running integration tests in parallel, and isolating staging environments, they reduced integration testing time by 75%, cut production incidents by 92%, increased release frequency from monthly to bi-weekly, and improved hospital staff satisfaction scores from 3.1 to 4.4. Support tickets dropped 73%, and zero critical defects were reported in the last 6 releases, enabling faster, safer, and more reliable healthcare software delivery.
